###############################################################################
# 06_6_wgcna_figure3_main_NatureAging_balanced_panels.R
#
# TITLE:
# Main WGCNA Figure 3 assembly using gene-collapsed modules - balanced Nature Aging layout
#
# PURPOSE:
# Generate a revised main WGCNA Figure 3 from outputs generated by Scripts 02–04.
# This v6.2 version preserves the Federica-aligned structure and adds editorial polish:
#   1) Remove DEP-direction from the WGCNA module portraits because module
#      membership is based on signed co-expression structure, not DEP direction.
#   2) Keep black in the module-trait and prioritization panels, but do not
#      force black into the hub/enrichment portraits because black has no
#      significant pathway enrichment in the current outputs.
#   3) Show only hub network + significant pathway enrichment for the
#      biologically interpretable portraits.
#   4) Improve journal-level visual style: cleaner TOM networks, at least
#      eight labelled hubs, softer edges, abbreviated pathway labels, larger
#      panel letters, and more compact layout.
#
# IMPORTANT:
# Adapted to:
#   C:/Users/mnpiz/Desktop/WGCNA_Workflow_april_V2
#
# Core modules for trait/prioritization visualization:
#   black, brown, yellow
#
# Core modules for biological portraits:
#   brown, yellow
#
# Black is retained in heatmap/prioritization but excluded from the biological
# portrait because enrichment_summary_by_module shows 0 significant GO/KEGG/Reactome
# terms for black.
#
# WGCNA level:
#   GENE-COLLAPSED, not aptamer-level.
###############################################################################

